text="The univalence axiom for elegant Reedy presheaves">The univalence axiom for elegant Reedy presheaves</fr:title><fr:taxon>Reference</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2015</fr:year></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="mikeshulman.xml"
addr="mikeshulman"
title="Mike Shulman">Mike Shulman</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="doi">10.4310/HHA.2015.v17.n2.a6</fr:meta><fr:meta
name="venue">Homology, Homotopy and Applications</fr:meta><fr:meta
name="bibtex"><![CDATA[@article{shulman-2015-elegant,
  author = {Shulman, Michael},
  year = {2015},
  doi = {10.4310/HHA.2015.v17.n2.a6},
  eprint = {1307.6248},
  eprintclass = {math.AT},
  eprinttype = {arXiv},
  issue = {2},
  journal = {Homology, Homotopy and Applications},
  pages = {81--106},
  title = {The Univalence Axiom for Elegant Reedy Presheaves},
  volume = {17},
}]]></fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We show that <fr:link
type="local"
href="vladimirvoevodsky.xml"
addr="vladimirvoevodsky"
title="Vladimir Voevodsky">Voevodsky</fr:link>’s univalence axiom for homotopy type theory is valid in categories of simplicial presheaves on elegant Reedy categories. In addition to diagrams on inverse categories, as considered in previous work of the author, this includes bisimplicial sets and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Theta _n]]></fr:tex>-spaces. This has potential applications to the study of homotopical models for higher categories.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
